        <h2>10 Hadiths to Inspire and Uplift</h2>
        <p>1. "The best among you are those who have the best manners and character." - Sahih Bukhari</p>
        <p>2. "Whoever believes in Allah and the Last Day, let him speak good or remain silent." - Sahih Muslim</p>
        <p>3. "The strong one is not the one who is strong in wrestling, but the one who controls himself when angry." - Sahih Bukhari</p>
        <p>4. "Kindness is a mark of faith, and whoever is not kind has no faith." - Sahih Muslim</p>
        <p>5. "Whoever shows you kindness, repay him with kindness." - Sahih Muslim</p>
        <p>6. "A Muslim is the one who avoids harming others with his tongue and hands." - Sahih Bukhari</p>
        <p>7. "Do not let your hatred of a people incite you to injustice." - Quran 5:8</p>
        <p>8. "The best of you are those who are the most beneficial to others." - Daraqutni</p>
        <p>9. "He who does not show mercy will not be shown mercy." - Sahih Bukhari</p>
        <p>10. "Abuse and bad language are signs of ignorance." - Sahih Bukhari</p>
